<br>
Just a little more notice and I'm sure you will get some assistance.<br>
<br>
As an asside, CoM is a fantastic raid practice zone for a smaller guild. You should be able to do quite well with 10 or so people over L50. We too had to venture there for numerous members, but often brought along our mid 40s members for raid tactics training. You wouldn't believe how quickly players in their mid 40s learn to pay attention, follow directions, and let the MA maintain agro when hunting Black Reavers! In addition, Harmony of Nature will land on the Black Reavers. We managed to single pull all the black reavers (except the last one I think) with this technique... and it makes for some fun &amp; exciting playing for the lucky Ranger/Druid puller! <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=457258"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Rinalthelis Wolfbrother</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.ancientadventurers.org">&lt;Ancient Adventurers&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
